      <section name="Download">
      <p>
        Jadabs is currently distributed in two versions. The minimal
        version includes the OSGi/dAOP/Jxme/RemoteFW and
        can be used on small devices in a distributed 
        environment. In the full version we added all the Knopflerfish
        services running on the AOP framework and a runtime AOP implementation.
        The full versions need to be run on a more powerfull node like laptop.
      </p>
      
      <table>
          <tr><th>configuration</th><th>Description</th><th>AOP</th><th>download</th></tr>
          
          <tr>
          	<td>minimal</td>
          	<td>OSGi/dAOP, JXME, RemoteFW</td>
          	<td>AspectJ/Nanning</td>
          	<td><a href="../releases/">jadabs-x.x.x-minimal.tar.gz</a></td>
          </tr>
          
          <tr>
          	<td>full</td>
          	<td>OSGi/dAOP, JXME, RemoteFW, all Knopflerfish Bundles</td>
          	<td>AspectJ/Nanning</td>
          	<td><a href="../releases/">jadabs-x.x.x-full.tar.gz</a></td>
          </tr>
          
          <tr>
          	<td>full-prose</td>
          	<td>OSGi/dAOP/Prose, JXME, RemoteFW, all Knopflerfish Bundles</td>
          	<td>AspectJ/Nanning/Prose</td>
          	<td><a href="../releases/">jadabs-x.x.x-fullprose.tar.gz</a></td>
          </tr>
          
      </table>
      
    </section>
      
  	<section name="Start">
		<p>
			For a Quick-Start download one of the above releases.
		</p>
		
		<table><tr><th>Default Execution</th></tr></table>
<source><![CDATA[
linux> runpeer.sh
or
win32> runpeer.bat
]]></source>

    <table><tr><th>Configured Execution</th></tr></table>
    <p>
        For a special configuration see table below and start accordingly.
    </p>
    
<source><![CDATA[
linux> runpeer.sh <configuration>
or
win32> runpeer.bat <configuration>
]]></source>



  	</section>
  	
  	<section name="Configuration">
  	    <p>
  	        Depending on which version you downloaded you have different possibilities to 
  	        start the container.
  	    </p>
  	    <p>
  	        Depending on which version you downloaded you have different possibilities to 
  	        start the container.
  	    </p>
  	
  	<table>
          <tr><th>Download</th><th>Configuration</th><th>Bundles</th><th>Description</th></tr>
          
          <tr>
          <td>minimal</td>
          <td>init.xargs (default for all)</td>
          <td>OSGi/dAOP, JXME, RemoteFW</td>
            <td>
              <p>
                  This configuration starts the dynamic lightweight container 
                  which can be administrated remotely.
              </p>
              <p>
                  This version has a very small footprint and can be easely run on a 
                  PDA with a Java VM compatible to Java 1.3, e.g. J2ME/CDC on an iPAQ.
              </p>
            </td>
          </tr>
                    
          <tr>
          <td>full</td>
          <td>init-gui-linux.xargs, init-gui-win32.xargs</td>
          <td>OSGi/dAOP, JXME, RemoteFW, MainGUI</td>
            <td>
              <p>
                  This configuration starts the dynamic lightweight container with
                  a simple GUI console to do remote administration.
              </p>
              <p>
                  Use the -linux.xargs for a linux machine and -win32.xargs for
                  a WindowsXP machine.
              </p>
            </td>
          </tr>
          
          <tr>
          <td>full</td>
          <td>init-kf.xargs</td>
          <td>OSGi/dAOP, JXME, RemoteFW, all Knopflerfish Bundles</td>
            <td>
              <p>
                  This configuration starts the dynamic lightweight container with
                  the Knopflerfish GUI including the remote framework for administration.
              </p>
            </td>
          </tr>
          
          <tr>
          <td>full-prose</td>
          <td>
              <ul>
                  <li>init.xargs prose</li>
                  <li>init-kf.xargs prose</li>
                  <li>init-gui-linux.xargs prose</li>
              </ul>
          </td>
          <td>OSGi/dAOP/Prose, JXME, RemoteFW, all Knopflerfish Bundles</td>
            <td>
              <p>
                  This configuration starts the dynamic lightweight container running
                  with PROSE including the remote framework for administration. With the
                  second configuration (init-kf prose) the Knopflerfish GUI is started
              </p>
            </td>
          </tr>
          
    </table>
  	
  	</section>
  	
